      ],
      "message": "fuzz: Add fuzz-only build mode option for targets\n\nIntroduce an option for fuzz targets to require BUILD_FOR_FUZZING=ON.\nThis ensures that targets like p2p_headers_presync, which need\nFUZZING_BUILD_MODE_UNSAFE_FOR_PRODUCTION set, are built correctly.\n\nWhen BUILD_FOR_FUZZING is enabled:\n- Disables all non-fuzzing build targets\n- Forces BUILD_FUZZ_BINARY=ON\n- Sets FUZZING_BUILD_MODE_UNSAFE_FOR_PRODUCTION\n- Enables ABORT_ON_FAILED_ASSUME\n\nThis change simplifies the setup for current and future fuzz harnesses\nthat require specific build configurations for proper functionality.\nThis also adds a runtime check to print a message and exit if a target\nrequires BUILD_FOR_FUZZING but it's not set.",
      "committer": {
